OL,3,CWhy this pub landlord gets the Freedom
OL,4,Cof Derby honour
OL,6,FThe landlord has also achieved
OL,7,Fimpressive rowing and walking feats in
OL,8,Fthe name of charity.
OL,10,FBefore being voted to receive the
OL,11,Fhonour, the motion read: "Council
OL,12,Fnotes the exceptional charitable
OL,13,Ffundraising undertaken by Mr Kirk, who
OL,14,Fhas raised over #120,000 for the Royal
OL,15,FBritish Legion.
OL,17,FAs landlord of The Neptune, he has
OL,18,Fraised more money for the annual poppy
OL,19,Fappeal than any other public house in
OL,20,Fthe UK.
